Program: Discovery
Title: Embryogenesis
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxgj
Last Broadcast Date: 04 August 1999
Embryogenesis is the process by which the embryo is formed. It refers to the period from the fertilization of the egg cell (ovum) by a sperm cell, (spermatozoon) to the formation of a multicellular embryo. The process involves an incredible arrangement of billions of cells